1
00:01:57,735 --> 00:01:59,612
I love you, Billy.

2
00:02:03,532 --> 00:02:05,868
I love you too, Mommy.

3
00:02:12,249 --> 00:02:13,584
Night-night.

4
00:02:16,837 --> 00:02:18,297
Sleep tight.

5
00:02:21,217 --> 00:02:23,677
Don't let the bedbugs bite.

6
00:02:25,471 --> 00:02:28,891
I'll see you in the morning light.

7
00:02:39,735 --> 00:02:41,445
I love you.

8
00:03:03,467 --> 00:03:06,720
They're going to make me an assistant
art director. So Kenny says:

9
00:03:06,929 --> 00:03:09,431
"You get yourself a Burberry coat.

10
00:03:09,723 --> 00:03:13,310
If you're gonna be Madison Avenue,
you have to look it."

11
00:03:13,561 --> 00:03:16,063
Saturday afternoon, I go out,
and it's cold.

12
00:03:16,355 --> 00:03:19,358
I go to this place
that specializes in Burberrys...

13
00:03:19,650 --> 00:03:22,319
...and say, " I want a Burberry coat,
37 short."

14
00:03:22,611 --> 00:03:25,447
They put it on,
and I look beautiful in it.

15
00:03:25,739 --> 00:03:26,907
I say, " I'll buy it."

16
00:03:27,157 --> 00:03:29,326
And right then, I start to sweat.

17
00:03:29,577 --> 00:03:33,622
I take my checkbook out, start to
sign the check, and my hand shakes...

18
00:03:33,914 --> 00:03:35,708
...because I'm so scared.

19
00:03:35,958 --> 00:03:37,418
- Good night.
- Where you going?

20
00:03:37,668 --> 00:03:41,463
- I gotta get home.
- Oh, Jesus, I gotta go.

21
00:03:41,714 --> 00:03:43,007
Okay, so let me finish.

22
00:03:43,299 --> 00:03:45,801
So I sign it,
and my hand starts shaking...

23
00:03:47,344 --> 00:03:50,931
Who is this? Danny, right?
Taxi!

24
00:03:51,181 --> 00:03:55,477
- Come on, I gotta tell you something.
- I can't. I gotta get home.

25
00:03:55,728 --> 00:03:58,397
Gotta talk to you
about something important.

26
00:03:58,689 --> 00:04:02,109
I'm putting you in charge
of the Mid-Atlantic account.

27
00:04:23,964 --> 00:04:27,051
By the end of the year, we'll
have them up to 10 million.

28
00:04:27,301 --> 00:04:30,554
If this campaign works out the way
I know it will...

29
00:04:30,804 --> 00:04:32,681
...they'll offer me a partnership.

30
00:04:32,890 --> 00:04:34,266
That's terrific!

31
00:04:34,475 --> 00:04:38,854
When that happens, I just want you
to know I'm taking you along.

32
00:04:40,189 --> 00:04:44,109
Wow! Wow! That's terrific.

33
00:05:01,669 --> 00:05:03,629
Joanna.

34
00:05:04,296 --> 00:05:06,006
I'm home.

35
00:05:09,093 --> 00:05:12,429
I forgot my keys. I gotta call
the office before they go.

36
00:05:12,680 --> 00:05:16,183
Jo, you're gonna be real proud
of me. I got good news.

37
00:05:18,686 --> 00:05:21,605
- Ted.
- One second. Let me just do this.

38
00:05:25,276 --> 00:05:28,529
You know Jack Edwards in accounting?
He committed suicide.

39
00:05:28,779 --> 00:05:30,823
Yeah, hi. Ted Kramer.

40
00:05:31,115 --> 00:05:34,910
I gotta get those photos from
the retoucher by tomorrow morning.

41
00:05:35,202 --> 00:05:37,872
- I'm leaving you.
- Honey, please. I can't hear.

42
00:05:39,582 --> 00:05:42,418
Okay, you too. Thanks a lot.
See you tomorrow.

43
00:05:43,043 --> 00:05:44,503
Did you guys eat?

44
00:05:44,753 --> 00:05:45,629
I'm leaving you.

45
00:05:48,757 --> 00:05:50,467
Here are my keys.

46
00:05:50,759 --> 00:05:53,846
Here's my American Express,
my Bloomingdale's card...

47
00:05:54,096 --> 00:05:57,933
...my checkbook. I've taken
$2000 out of our savings account.

48
00:05:58,183 --> 00:06:00,394
That's what I had when we got married.

49
00:06:00,686 --> 00:06:03,439
- Is this a joke?
- Here's the cleaning, laundry ticket.

50
00:06:03,689 --> 00:06:05,816
You can pick them both up
on Saturday.

51
00:06:06,066 --> 00:06:08,527
- You. You have to pick them up.
- What's wrong?

52
00:06:08,819 --> 00:06:12,573
I paid the rent, the Con Ed bill,
and the phone bill, so...

53
00:06:12,865 --> 00:06:14,575
You really pick your times to...

54
00:06:18,829 --> 00:06:22,666
I'm sorry I was late, but I was
busy making a living, all right?

55
00:06:23,500 --> 00:06:26,754
Come on, okay? Can we stop now?

56
00:06:27,004 --> 00:06:29,089
So that's everything.

57
00:06:34,345 --> 00:06:36,055
Enough, enough. All right?

58
00:06:36,305 --> 00:06:38,265
What are you doing?

59
00:06:38,599 --> 00:06:42,186
Where are you going? Just tell me
what I did that's so terrible.

60
00:06:42,436 --> 00:06:43,729
- It's not you.
- Then what?

61
00:06:44,021 --> 00:06:46,023
It's me. It's my fault.

62
00:06:46,523 --> 00:06:47,983
You married the wrong person.

63
00:06:48,234 --> 00:06:50,653
- I can't hack it.
- Let's just go inside.

64
00:06:50,945 --> 00:06:52,947
I can't, I tried.
I swear...

65
00:06:53,239 --> 00:06:56,075
Joanna, please, just... I'm sorry.

66
00:06:56,367 --> 00:07:01,455
- No, please don't make me go in there.
- I just want to talk.

67
00:07:01,747 --> 00:07:04,250
If you do, I swear, one day...

68
00:07:04,500 --> 00:07:07,002
...l'll go right out the window.
- Oh, please.

69
00:07:07,294 --> 00:07:09,547
Come on, now. What about Billy?

70
00:07:13,509 --> 00:07:16,887
I'm not taking him with me.
I'm no good for him.

71
00:07:17,429 --> 00:07:18,806
I'm terrible with him.

72
00:07:19,098 --> 00:07:21,934
I have no patience.

73
00:07:22,142 --> 00:07:24,186
He's better off without me.

74
00:07:26,397 --> 00:07:27,856
Joanna, please.

75
00:07:32,736 --> 00:07:35,030
And I don't love you anymore.

76
00:07:37,032 --> 00:07:38,993
- Where are you going?
- I don't know.

77
00:08:13,444 --> 00:08:16,780
Hi, Margaret. This is Ted.
Is my wife there?

78
00:08:16,989 --> 00:08:20,159
Yeah. Joanna come in?

79
00:08:20,409 --> 00:08:24,705
We had a little fight. I thought
she might have stopped by.

80
00:08:24,914 --> 00:08:28,250
If she comes in, tell her to come up
or just give me a ring.

81
00:08:30,127 --> 00:08:34,256
Don't worry. She didn't take
her suitcase. She won't get very far.

82
00:08:35,466 --> 00:08:38,802
I got work to do.
If she comes in, tell her to call me.

83
00:08:45,893 --> 00:08:47,436
It's about time.

84
00:08:50,481 --> 00:08:53,317
Joanna, that's the most insensitive...
Hi, Margaret.

85
00:08:53,609 --> 00:08:57,404
- She packed a suitcase?
- Look, it's nothing serious, really.

86
00:08:57,696 --> 00:08:59,657
She tell you where she was going?

87
00:08:59,907 --> 00:09:02,660
- You tell me.
- How would I know? I wasn't here.

88
00:09:02,910 --> 00:09:06,413
Clearly, you two had many
talks about my shortcomings...

89
00:09:06,622 --> 00:09:09,625
...which I haven't been privy to.
And I'd love to talk...

90
00:09:09,917 --> 00:09:13,170
...but I have a major presentation
in the morning...

91
00:09:13,420 --> 00:09:16,257
...and I gotta get my work done.
So please allow me...

92
00:09:16,507 --> 00:09:19,093
You don't realize
we have a serious problem.

93
00:09:19,343 --> 00:09:22,263
Wrong. Me. I got the problem.
All you gotta do is...

94
00:09:22,555 --> 00:09:24,890
...go out the door and go back to bed.

95
00:09:25,349 --> 00:09:27,851
- The fact is...
- For six months...

96
00:09:28,143 --> 00:09:31,689
...l've been spitting blood to get
this agency its biggest account.

97
00:09:31,981 --> 00:09:34,024
And at five, we got it.

98
00:09:34,858 --> 00:09:39,321
At eight, the vice president tells me
I'll be the next creative director.

99
00:09:39,572 --> 00:09:42,116
I come through this door
to share with my wife...

100
00:09:42,366 --> 00:09:46,036
...one of the five best days
of my life, and she looks at me...

101
00:09:46,328 --> 00:09:48,914
...and tells me she doesn't want
to live with me!

102
00:09:54,461 --> 00:09:57,047
Can't you understand
what she's done to me?

103
00:09:59,049 --> 00:10:02,469
She loused up one of the five
best days of your life.

104
00:10:06,432 --> 00:10:08,767
You're terrific. Boy, you're...

105
00:10:09,059 --> 00:10:11,020
Thanks very much, really.

106
00:10:12,730 --> 00:10:14,273
Sisterhood.

107
00:10:14,523 --> 00:10:16,734
Thank you for coming
to cheer me up, but...

108
00:10:17,067 --> 00:10:19,028
I didn't come to cheer you up.

109
00:10:19,278 --> 00:10:21,155
I'm concerned about Joanna.

110
00:10:21,739 --> 00:10:25,242
Maybe you can be concerned
in the privacy of your own apartment.

111
00:10:26,243 --> 00:10:30,539
Joanna and I never had any problems
until you and Charley split up.

112
00:10:30,831 --> 00:10:32,791
Oh, I don't believe you.

113
00:10:33,042 --> 00:10:34,835
Just tell me the truth, okay?

114
00:10:35,085 --> 00:10:36,712
Did you set her up to this?

115
00:10:37,004 --> 00:10:38,881
No, I didn't put her up to this.

116
00:10:39,173 --> 00:10:41,550
- Give her a little pep talk?
- No, I didn't.

117
00:10:41,842 --> 00:10:43,802
Joanna and I talk a great deal.

118
00:10:44,094 --> 00:10:46,180
And Joanna is a very unhappy woman.

119
00:10:46,472 --> 00:10:50,935
And it took a lot of courage for her
to walk out of here.

120
00:10:51,185 --> 00:10:54,188
How much courage does it take
to walk out on your kid?

121
00:12:08,512 --> 00:12:09,889
Where's Mommy?

122
00:12:10,180 --> 00:12:11,807
- What?
- Where's Mommy?

123
00:12:12,016 --> 00:12:13,475
What time is it?

124
00:12:14,727 --> 00:12:19,523
The little hand's on the 7, the big
hand's on the 9. Where's Mommy?

125
00:12:21,358 --> 00:12:26,405
Oh, God. Okay, I'm gonna tell you.
You want to know where Mommy is?

126
00:12:26,655 --> 00:12:29,992
- She's supposed to take me to school.
- She told me to do it.

127
00:12:30,201 --> 00:12:32,161
Okay, I'll tell you where she went.

128
00:12:32,369 --> 00:12:36,040
You know when you and your friends
don't get along and fight?

129
00:12:36,290 --> 00:12:38,876
And you want to go and be alone
for a while?

130
00:12:39,126 --> 00:12:41,795
Sometimes Mommy and Daddy
don't get along...

131
00:12:42,004 --> 00:12:45,758
...and one of them wants to go
and be by themselves for a while.

132
00:12:46,008 --> 00:12:48,302
- When is Mommy coming back?
- Soon.

133
00:12:48,594 --> 00:12:52,056
Now we are gonna have breakfast!
Okay? Just you and me.

134
00:12:52,348 --> 00:12:54,475
- What do you want?
- French toast.

135
00:12:54,850 --> 00:12:56,810
You want French toast, you got it.

136
00:12:57,061 --> 00:13:00,231
Put up a little water for Daddy
to have some coffee.

137
00:13:00,481 --> 00:13:03,484
We got how many eggs?
Two for you and two for me.

138
00:13:03,776 --> 00:13:04,777
We got milk.

139
00:13:05,069 --> 00:13:06,445
We got butter.

140
00:13:06,737 --> 00:13:08,531
We got $5.

141
00:13:08,739 --> 00:13:11,200
I got $5.
Here, you sit here.

142
00:13:12,034 --> 00:13:14,787
Okay, can you be my number one helper?

143
00:13:16,622 --> 00:13:17,790
Watch this. One hand.

144
00:13:18,624 --> 00:13:20,000
Here we go.

145
00:13:20,209 --> 00:13:23,045
Did you know that all
the best chefs are men?

146
00:13:23,295 --> 00:13:26,465
Isn't this terrific?
We gotta do this more often.

147
00:13:26,674 --> 00:13:29,134
- You dropped some shell in it.
- That's okay.

148
00:13:29,593 --> 00:13:33,013
Makes it crunchier.
You like it crunchy, don't you?

149
00:13:33,222 --> 00:13:37,059
Why don't you beat them,
and I'll get everything else going.

150
00:13:37,351 --> 00:13:39,311
- What time is school?
- 8:30.

151
00:13:39,562 --> 00:13:43,691
Gotta get the show on the road.
I gotta shower, shave and shampoo.

152
00:13:43,983 --> 00:13:45,025
I got people to see.

153
00:13:45,317 --> 00:13:47,820
And Daddy's gotta bring home
the bacon...

154
00:13:48,070 --> 00:13:49,530
...and he's gotta cook it.

155
00:13:49,989 --> 00:13:52,992
We're having a good time!
Where does Mommy keep the...?

156
00:13:53,409 --> 00:13:55,536
- In the stove.
- The pan. The stove.

157
00:13:57,830 --> 00:13:59,373
First, we need a nice fire.

158
00:14:00,291 --> 00:14:02,334
No, you're not doing it right.

159
00:14:02,626 --> 00:14:06,046
Look, you gotta do it fast. See?
It's the wrist.

160
00:14:06,297 --> 00:14:08,173
So the gucky part dissolves.

161
00:14:08,382 --> 00:14:12,136
Then you take the bread, and we...

162
00:14:12,428 --> 00:14:14,054
We...

163
00:14:15,055 --> 00:14:18,142
We fold the French toast.
That's what we do.

164
00:14:18,434 --> 00:14:21,937
- I think you forgot milk.
- I didn't. Milk comes last.

165
00:14:23,230 --> 00:14:25,900
When you're having a good time
you forget things.

166
00:14:26,609 --> 00:14:29,778
I just wanted to see
if you're paying attention.

167
00:14:30,362 --> 00:14:33,824
Fun, isn't it? When's the last
time Mommy let you in the kitchen?

168
00:14:34,116 --> 00:14:35,576
I don't like it in pieces.

169
00:14:35,826 --> 00:14:39,872
It tastes the same whether it's in
pieces or whole. Bread is bread.

170
00:14:40,206 --> 00:14:42,541
Besides, French toast
is always folded.

171
00:14:42,833 --> 00:14:46,003
In the best restaurants,
you see folded French toast.

172
00:14:46,337 --> 00:14:48,214
You get more bites that way.

173
00:14:50,049 --> 00:14:53,219
And while that's going,
Daddy's gonna make coffee.

174
00:14:53,510 --> 00:14:55,054
You having a good time?

175
00:14:55,304 --> 00:14:58,849
I don't remember the last
time I had such a good time.

176
00:14:59,850 --> 00:15:01,727
Daddy's gonna make himself coffee.

177
00:15:01,977 --> 00:15:04,355
- That's too much!
- No, I like it strong.

178
00:15:04,647 --> 00:15:06,774
Mommy always makes it too weak.

179
00:15:08,984 --> 00:15:10,945
Can I have some orange juice?

180
00:15:11,779 --> 00:15:14,073
Right. One OJ coming up
for the kid.

181
00:15:16,617 --> 00:15:18,077
Daddy, it's burning!

182
00:15:18,869 --> 00:15:20,496
- What?
- It's burning!

183
00:15:22,456 --> 00:15:25,459
Damn it! Goddamn her!

184
00:15:28,587 --> 00:15:30,297
Oh, shit.

185
00:15:32,550 --> 00:15:36,262
Just take it easy.
Everything is fine. We're terrific.

186
00:15:36,554 --> 00:15:38,013
Just...

187
00:15:39,431 --> 00:15:42,601
Just take it easy.
Nothing is the matter.

188
00:15:46,355 --> 00:15:47,731
- What?
- Your hand's sweaty.

189
00:15:48,023 --> 00:15:50,526
- When's Mommy coming back?
- Soon. I told you.

190
00:15:50,818 --> 00:15:54,154
- Is she gonna pick me up?
- Probably. If she doesn't, I will.

191
00:15:54,363 --> 00:15:56,240
- What if you forget?
- I won't.

192
00:15:56,490 --> 00:15:59,827
- What if you get run over?
- Mommy will pick you up.

193
00:16:00,077 --> 00:16:02,204
- Miss! What grade are you in?
- First.

194
00:16:02,454 --> 00:16:04,957
This is Billy Kramer.
He's in first grade.

195
00:16:05,207 --> 00:16:07,543
Take care of him. I gotta
get a taxi, I'm late. Taxi!

196
00:16:08,377 --> 00:16:09,753
Taxi!

197
00:16:12,590 --> 00:16:15,426
- Congratulations about Mid-Atlantic.
- Thanks.

198
00:16:15,718 --> 00:16:19,096
- Congratulations.
- Is the stuff back from the retoucher?

199
00:16:19,346 --> 00:16:21,640
- Great news, Ted.
- Thanks a lot.

200
00:16:21,932 --> 00:16:24,310
Morning. 11:00, meeting
with Airwick...

201
00:16:24,602 --> 00:16:27,855
- Where's the stuff from the retoucher?
- Right here.

202
00:16:28,564 --> 00:16:29,940
- Did my wife call?
- No.

203
00:16:30,232 --> 00:16:33,485
You're gonna have to cancel
the Airwick at 11:30.

204
00:17:04,725 --> 00:17:07,978
She's never gone this far before,
but in the past...

205
00:17:08,229 --> 00:17:11,065
...l've known
when she's upset because...

206
00:17:11,315 --> 00:17:12,942
...she gets very quiet.

207
00:17:13,234 --> 00:17:16,737
Our pattern has been that I've said,
"What's the matter?"...

208
00:17:16,987 --> 00:17:18,864
...and she'll kind of sit on it.

209
00:17:19,156 --> 00:17:22,159
But in the last few weeks,
maybe couple of months...

210
00:17:22,409 --> 00:17:26,330
...since we've been going crazy
with this account, I've been remiss.

211
00:17:26,622 --> 00:17:31,961
And I just didn't look at the writing
on the wall, so she's kind of...

212
00:17:32,503 --> 00:17:36,090
I think this is a way
of making me stop, look and say:

213
00:17:36,298 --> 00:17:38,425
" I'm as important as your work."

214
00:17:40,719 --> 00:17:42,763
Is there another guy?

215
00:17:44,807 --> 00:17:47,560
I don't think so.
She's not the type.

216
00:17:47,810 --> 00:17:50,646
She's got this friend, Margaret,
downstairs...

217
00:17:51,397 --> 00:17:55,693
...you know, women's lib.
I think they may have cooked this up.

218
00:17:56,735 --> 00:17:57,736
It worked.

219
00:17:59,113 --> 00:18:00,489
I'm going crazy!

220
00:18:00,781 --> 00:18:02,950
Look, not to worry.

221
00:18:03,200 --> 00:18:04,743
She'll be back.

222
00:18:04,994 --> 00:18:07,329
I didn't know it would happen to me!

223
00:18:08,372 --> 00:18:09,832
Don't let it get you down.

224
00:18:10,124 --> 00:18:13,544
I know she'll be back.
I'm terrific, really.

225
00:18:16,171 --> 00:18:19,008
- You do have a problem, Ted.
- Yeah, what's that?

226
00:18:21,927 --> 00:18:23,804
What are you gonna do about Billy?

227
00:18:25,598 --> 00:18:29,518
This just happened last night.
I'm sure when Joanna comes back...

228
00:18:29,768 --> 00:18:31,979
It's none of my business.
I'll butt out.

229
00:18:32,229 --> 00:18:34,815
Listen, I want to hear your thoughts.

230
00:18:35,107 --> 00:18:38,277
I appreciate you
taking the time to talk to me.

231
00:18:38,986 --> 00:18:43,032
May sound a little rough, but...

232
00:18:43,324 --> 00:18:47,620
...I think you ought to send Billy away
to stay with relatives for a while.

233
00:18:48,078 --> 00:18:50,497
You mean, until Joanna comes back?

234
00:18:51,373 --> 00:18:53,626
Suppose Joanna doesn't come back?

235
00:18:56,962 --> 00:18:58,672
Gee, I don't know...

236
00:18:58,923 --> 00:19:00,466
Ted, listen to me.

237
00:19:00,716 --> 00:19:05,971
I just told the boys upstairs you're
handling the Mid-Atlantic account.

238
00:19:06,222 --> 00:19:10,768
