677
00:54:34,378 --> 00:54:35,296
Such as?

678
00:54:37,465 --> 00:54:41,594
No, really, I'd really like to
know what you learned.

679
00:54:46,766 --> 00:54:50,728
I've learned
that I love my little boy.

680
00:54:52,063 --> 00:54:55,233
And that I'm capable of taking
care of him.

681
00:54:55,483 --> 00:54:56,943
What do you mean?

682
00:54:59,612 --> 00:55:00,655
I want my son.

683
00:55:01,614 --> 00:55:02,698
You can't have him.

684
00:55:02,990 --> 00:55:05,243
Don't get defensive. Don't bully me.

685
00:55:05,534 --> 00:55:06,911
I'm not getting defensive.

686
00:55:07,370 --> 00:55:08,996
Who walked out 15 months ago?

687
00:55:09,288 --> 00:55:11,457
I don't care. I'm still his mother.

688
00:55:11,832 --> 00:55:13,000
From 3000 miles away.

689
00:55:13,251 --> 00:55:16,420
Because you sent post cards gives
you the right to come back?

690
00:55:16,671 --> 00:55:18,464
I never stopped wanting him.

691
00:55:18,673 --> 00:55:20,299
What makes you sure he wants you?

692
00:55:20,716 --> 00:55:22,510
What makes you sure he doesn't?

693
00:55:24,011 --> 00:55:27,014
We're gonna sit here and
bat this back and forth.

694
00:55:27,223 --> 00:55:29,392
- It's like old times.
- You can't deny me...

695
00:55:29,642 --> 00:55:32,812
Don't tell me what I can or cannot do.

696
00:55:33,145 --> 00:55:36,315
- Don't talk to me that way.
- I anticipated this.

697
00:55:36,607 --> 00:55:38,901
Do what you have to.
I'll do what I have to.

698
00:55:39,193 --> 00:55:40,319
I'm sorry about this.

699
00:55:40,778 --> 00:55:42,405
Do what you have to do.

700
00:55:50,079 --> 00:55:53,749
I don't know the legal jargon for it,
but I think it's "desertion. "

701
00:55:54,041 --> 00:55:59,171
